===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|upbreiden}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ūpbreġdan}}, equivalent to {{af|en|up-|braid}}. Compare {{cog|en|umbraid|t=to upbraid}}, {{cog|is|bregða|t=to draw, brandish, braid, deviate from, change, break off, upbraid}}. See {{m|en|up}}, and {{m|en|braid}} {{qualifier|transitive}}.

